<reg_short_dscr>:
LC-PLL configuration register 4
------------------------------
<reg_public_text>:
LC-PLL configuration register 4
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
LCPLL Test Mode
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0:  Normal Operation
1: Adds another Divide by 4 on feedback divider (ATE test only)
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Time limit for phase lock detector.  
It is the number of clock counts of reference clock.  
Within this time, if the number of error is larger than ERRBUF, the lock detector will trigger LOS signal. 

Good value is 0x14
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Error Buffer. Set to 0x1.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Select source of the LCPLL integer divider value N used for VCO frequency control:

When N_SRC_SEL is '0' the value of N is controlled by the reference clock selection strapping pins and the LCPLL_CONFIG4.N register is ignored.

When N_SRC_SEL is '1' the value of N is controlled by the LCPLL_CONFIG4.N register.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Use strapping pins to select N value
1: Use LCPLL_CONFIG4.N register to select N value
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
N integer divider.  VCO freq = REFCLKIN * N. Target is 10GHz.

Minimum: 32 (0x20)
Maximum: 2^16: 1 

The configured value is ignored if LCPLL_CONFIG4.N_SRC_SEL = '0'
------------------------------
